#Scala 
There are mainly two different types of variables avaialble in Scala
val and var
-- val is immutable, once defined the value can't be changed.
-- var is mutable, value can be changed after defining the variable
-- semicolon ending is not necessary while declaring the variables
-- Initialization is mandataory while defining variables
example:
val i=10
i= i+10 // it will throw an error

var i=10
i= i+10 //it is valid

-- If the datatype is not defined based on the given data, datatype will be provided by scala

#Define variables with pre-defined datatype
syntax:
var/val variable_name: data type =value
val i: Int =10

-- Different datatypes avaialble in scala are Byte, Short, Int, Long, Float, Double, Char, String, Boolean
val i: Long = 10L
val i: Long = 10l
val j: Float = 10.0F
val j: Float = 10.0f
